Coat chicken pieces with flour. In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil on both sides. In a bowl, combine the water, rice, milk, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper. Pour into a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Top with chicken. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350 degrees F for 35-45 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender. Sprinkle with parsley.